result.execSummary:
The defendant Zachary A Olivera Graham was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
8:58 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jon Wilsnack.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to Count 1 & 2 on 2015CF96 and count 2 on 2015CM194, and enter into a plea diversion agreement on count 1 on 2015CF96 and probation sentence on the other counts.  State concurs.  Statement by Atty Wilsnack - defendant will waive the preliminary hearing on 2015CF96.  Defendant concurs.  Court instructs the defendant regarding his right to a preliminary examination.  Defendant waives his right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.

State files an information with the court.  Attorney Wilsnack and defendant acknowledge receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Atty Wilsnack enters a plea of NO CONTEST on behalf of the defendant per the plea questionnaire.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on counts 1 & 2 as charged on 2015CF96 and count 2 as charged on 2015CM194.  Court orders count 3 on 2015CF96 and count 1 on 2015CM194 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction on count 1 on 2015CF96 be withheld and adjourns pending compliance with  the Plea Diversion Agreement - 2 years.  Court orders judgment of conviction be entered here today on counts 2 on each case.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Wilsnack.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

2015CF96 (count 2) & 2015CM194 (Count 2) - EACH COUNT

SWD and places the defendant on probation for 2 years.

CONDITIONS:

-Court costs.
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent.
-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

Court grants the defendant Sentence credit on the felony as determined by the jail.

Court adjourned at 9:15 a.m.
